name: Do Nothing Till You Hear from Me
comments: Duke Ellington and His Orchestra (with Al Hibbler) first performed this song at the Hurricane Club in New York on August 14th, 1943 and on numerous later occasions. Some of these recordings were subsequently made available. The song consists of part of the tune of "Concerto for Cootie" with lyrics added by Bob Russell.
